# Use SLURM-Safe Execution

This project runs on an interactive node of a SLURM cluster.

- Do not run long, intensive, or training jobs directly on the current node.
- Keep direct terminal commands lightweight unless the user clearly wants a quick local check.
- For substantial work, use `srun` for interactive runs or `sbatch` for scheduled jobs.
- When GPUs are needed, prefer `--partition=gpu` to use the first available A100 or V100.
- Request RTX Pro 6000 GPUs only when they are specifically needed, using `--gpus-per-node=rtx_pro_6000:<count>`.

```bash
# ❌ BAD
uv run src/training/train.py --epochs 200
python large_experiment.py

# ✅ GOOD
srun --partition=gpu --gpus=1 uv run src/training/train.py --epochs 200
sbatch SLURM/train_unet_multi_input.sh

# ✅ RTX Pro 6000 only when explicitly needed
srun --partition=gpu --gpus-per-node=rtx_pro_6000:1 uv run script_that_requires_it.py
```
